Probabilistic Methods, Theory

The paper belongs to the sub-category of Probabilistic Methods because it uses probabilistic models to learn unions of rectangles. The authors use a Bayesian approach to model the probability of a point belonging to a rectangle and then use this model to learn the union of rectangles that best fits the data.

The paper also belongs to the sub-category of Theory because it provides a theoretical analysis of the problem of learning unions of rectangles. The authors prove that the problem is NP-hard and provide an algorithm that approximates the optimal solution. They also provide bounds on the approximation ratio of their algorithm.
